<refsect2 id="rygel-media-device-add-interface" role="function">
<title>rygel_media_device_add_interface ()</title>
<indexterm zone="rygel-media-device-add-interface"><primary>rygel_media_device_add_interface</primary></indexterm>
<programlisting><link linkend="void"><returnvalue>void</returnvalue></link>                rygel_media_device_add_interface    (<parameter><link linkend="RygelMediaDevice"><type>RygelMediaDevice</type></link> *self</parameter>,
                                                         <parameter>const <link linkend="gchar"><type>gchar</type></link> *iface</parameter>);</programlisting>
<para>
Add a network interface the device should listen on.
</para>
<para>
<para>If the network interface is not already up, it will be used as soon as it&apos;s ready, otherwise it&apos;s used right away.</para>
</para><variablelist role="params">
<varlistentry><term><parameter>self</parameter>&#160;:</term>
<listitem><simpara>the <link linkend="RygelMediaDevice"><type>RygelMediaDevice</type></link> instance</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><parameter>iface</parameter>&#160;:</term>
<listitem><simpara>Name of the network interface, e.g. eth0. <emphasis role="annotation">[<acronym>in</acronym>]</emphasis></simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect2>
